snippet.textDisplay:
So far, no cure has been found for the coronavirus. Residents of Wuhan have been trapped inside the city since January 23, 2020. They live in fear, as their lives are threatened by the epidemic. Falun Gong practitioners outside of China have been phoning them and giving them advice on how to stay safe.

For years, practitioners have been advising people to quit the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) and its affiliated organizations. The CCP has committed countless heinous crimes since it took power. When people join the CCP, they vow to give their lives to the Party. By withdrawing from the CCP, they are no longer are part of it and avoid being held accountable for its crimes.

Practitioners also advise Wuhan residents to sincerely say, “Falun Dafa is good, Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance is good.”

“Use My Real Name”
After Mr. Wang was infected with the coronavirus, he was grateful for the practitioner who got his number and phoned him. “I might be fine if I'd been treated in time, but I've been waiting for a hospital bed for days,” he said.

The practitioner advised him that, since there was no cure, he had to help himself. After he told her that he'd joined the Young Pioneers, she explained why millions of Chinese have quit the CCP organizations and offered to help him quit with an alias.

“Please help me quit with my real name,” he immediately replied.

Mr. Wang was very happy and repeatedly thanked the practitioner. She advised him to sincerely say, “Falun Dafa is good, Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance is good.”

Hospitalized Woman Quits the CCP
Ms. Zhu in Fangcang Hospital was moved when a practitioner phoned her. “I'm so excited to get a call from overseas!” she said. “I'm so miserable: My mother is in intensive care and my child and husband are quarantined.”

The practitioner told her to stay calm and remember to say, “Falun Dafa is good." After she understood the importance of quitting the CCP and its affiliated organizations, Ms. Zhu said that she’d joined the CCP when she was in college.

“Please help me quit,” she said. “I believe you. I want to stay safe and well!”
